parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS engages unnecessarily
causing the vehicle to skid or vibrate; the brake pedal pulsates or goes to the floor; the vehicle takes longer to stop; the brakes lock up; the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads and rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Uneven wear on brake pads; rapid wear on brake pads; brake pads need to be replaced frequently; rotors need to be resurfaced or replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause the ABS to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS engages unnecessarily; the brake pedal pulsates or goes to the floor; the vehicle takes longer to stop; the brakes lock up; the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake line or hub can cause the braking system to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks; brake pedal goes to the floor; the vehicle takes longer to stop; the brakes lock up; the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the heater fan quits
the ABS light turns on
the cruise control fails to operate
and the dash lights do not turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering to become difficult or impossible to control, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel jerks or pulls to one side
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering feels loose or sloppy
and the vehicle is difficult to control while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering sensor can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The steering becomes erratic or unpredictable
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel jerks or pulls to one side
and the vehicle is difficult to control while turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission shifts harshly
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
the transmission overheats
transmission fluid leaks
the vehicle makes a knocking or clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission shifts harshly
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
the transmission overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission fluid leaks can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to damage to other components and costly repairs. It can also cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
the transmission overheats
smoke coming from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Reverse gear failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle has no reverse gear
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle makes a clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause damage to other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The axle separates
the rear wheel comes off
the vehicle loses control.
